{
  "stem": "9168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In that trial, there were over 11,000 pages of court transcript.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I learned that, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for example, the entire foreign-- German foreign office documents were found by the Allied forces almost intact.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- there were tons of documents that-- that were even located in abandoned castle walls in Germany, where the Nazis had tried to hide this evidence.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were all represented by counsel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if-- and they were given time to get their own counsel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if they had none, the American judges were prepared to appoint German counsel for them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Many of the German counsel were still members of the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And they all entered their pleas without being allowed to make any statements.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not guilty.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They all entered pleas of not guilty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I don't believe that I had started the-- I do not remember this specifically, being in the courtroom at the time of the entry of the pleas.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I wanted to say first, in the high altitude experiment, these were approximately 200 experimental subjects, who were Russian and Polish Jews who-- and they were put into this experiment because they were termed professional criminals.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that meant they were professional criminals because they had been condemned for racial shame consisting of intercourse and marriage between non-Aryans and Aryans, which was the term given to pure-blooded Germans.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of that group of 200, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] there were 80-- 70 to 80 who died in the experiment, and the others were just-- it was just pure torture for them.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
